	<div class="About Us" id="AboutUs">
	<h2>About Us</h2>
		The Gastroenterology Division at Medanta’s Institute of Digestive and Hepatobiliary Sciences aims to 
		provide the best possible treatment to patients who come with advanced stage of diseases involving their digestive, 
		liver and pancreato-biliary tracts. We have advanced facilities and carry out majority of the major endoscopy and radiology
		 assisted procedures for gastrointestinal, liver and bilio-pancreatic disorders. 
		The unit also comprises of a Liver Clinic for early diagnosis and treatment of liver diseases along with gastrointestinal diseases.	
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="What we Treat" id="WhatweTreat?">
	<h2>What we Treat?</h2>
		At the Gastroenterology Division, we invest our efforts,
		 time, and skill into helping people overcome various digestive and hepatobiliary diseases.
		<br>
		<ul type="square">
		<li>Crohn’s Disease
		<li>Pancreatitis
		<li>Ulcerative Colitis
		<li>Celiac Disease
		<li>Liver cancer
		<li>Gastrointestinal bleeding
		<li>Chronic liver disease
		<li>Inflammatory Bowel Diseases
		</ul>
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	At the Gastroenterology Division of the Institute of Digestive and Hepatobiliary Sciences, we aim to make 
	our patients’ recovery gently yet as fast as possible with the help of latest technology used by our team of
	 doctors. We provide a platform where the gastroenterologists and surgeons work together as a team to use advanced 
	 diagnostic technologies. Our team provides the best possible care to patients from across the globe at an affordable cost.
Advanced medical and surgical care is primarily focused on safe and proven treatment of disorders
 related to the gastrointestinal tract. We perform diagnostic endoscopy and therapeutic endoscopy,
  colonoscopy, fluoroscopy and ERCP (Endoscopic Retrograde Cholangiopancreatography).
</div>
